<p>IV<br/>Old Ross is away in England at present doing a school of gunnery.  I miss him a lot as he is great company  -<br/>I have not been able to hear anything about Terence Wise &ndash; He would probably be over here now so I shall write to Horseferry Road &amp; try &amp; ascertain his address.  You ask me for a few suggestions as to Pat's kit &ndash; There is really nothing he could buy to advantage in Australia except a bed valise.  These used to be made very well by S. Walder, the Tent maker.  If he could get a good strong one it would last for all time, and be more comfortable than the ones bought in England or</p>
